Here is information as we host our first volleyball triangular of the season!

A reminder that some trafficking will look different, our concession stand will be limited, and we ask that you sit in 6 foot socially distanced groups by family.

We will ask that fans of the team not playing exit the gym to allow fans of the teams playing to watch as we will keep the gym at 50% capacity. We will have a video feed of the games available in the concession area.

Many other details on our safety procedures can be found in our Events & Activities document.

Thanks to all for following our new guidelines in order to continue to have activities!

post_text:
We have some exciting information to share!

Our administration team applied for a grant through the Nebraska Department of Environment and Energy to help us purchase a brand new bus for HPS. We have received official notice that we got the grant! These funds, with others, will allow us to purchase a 36 passenger activity bus with individual reclining seats, air conditioning, a wheelchair lift, two wheelchair spots on the bus, many safety features, and more!

This will be a great addition for field trips, activities, games, events, and more that we attend on the road!

Here is letter from the Department of Environment and Energy on our award to help us purchase this bus!

post_text:
Parent/Guardian(s) and Students:

Enrichment activities are updated for this week on our website!

Why do we do these?

Think of it this way. If you are a track athlete and you take off two months from any athletic activity, workouts, or practices, how will it feel when you come back to track? You will be behind others who have been working, but it's more about you! You will be behind of where you left off because your body isn't used to the work outs and remembering where it was at.

This is the same concept as education. We want to bridge the gap and make it as small as possible. Rather than looking at this as an "extra long summer break," we encourage families and students to complete the enrichment activities to help keep the mind in practice. Continue the "workouts" for the brain to help continue education and learning in order to pick up right where we left off when we return!

http://www.harvardcardinals.org/vnews/display.v/ART/5256ca2ebf315

Here is some health and safety information that we've recently put on our website to inform parents, patrons, and supporters of our district regarding health and safety related to the Coronavirus. We have been working with the Clay County Emergency Manager on details of the situation in the area and are doing what we can to best prevent the spread of any flu throughout our building. In addition, we've shared health tips with our faculty and staff as reminders and will update them accordingly should things progress.

Stay healthy!
